o drive-up movie screens, and 30 Supercharger stalls.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eTesla \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/3/14/17120634/tesla-permit-supercharger-restaurant-drive-in-elon-musk\"\u003egot the permit for the diner seven years ago\u003c/a\u003e. At the time, California was the de facto home of Tesla and a champion of its electric vehicles, but since then, the company has moved its headquarters to Texas, Musk has gotten into far-right politics with his \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/policy/620892/cpac-elon-musk-chainsaw-trump-steve-bannon\"\u003edeep involvement in the Trump Administration\u003c/a\u003e, and revenue is tanking \u003ca href=\"https://www.theverge.com/news/653645/tesla-q1-earnings-2025-revenue-profit-elon-musk\"\u003eas seen in today’s earnings report\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cform\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch2\u003eInstaller\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eA weekly newsletter by David Pierce designed to tell you everything you need to download, watch, read, listen to, and explore that fits in The Verge’s universe.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/form\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/main\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
